---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Rentier Digital"
  description="20 years in dev, now helping non-technical founders build and ship real products with AI."
>
  <article class="prose prose-invert mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-6">
      <img
        src="/avatar.png"
        alt="Phil"
        class="h-24 w-24 rounded-full border-2 border-white/10"
      />
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">About</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      I'm Phil — 20 years in software development, team leadership, and agile
      methods. I've been building products from A to Z for startups and
      scale-ups as a technical co-founder and CTO.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Rentier Digital</strong> is where I share what I know about
      building real products with AI. Not theory — practical guides, tools, and
      methods for solo builders and non-technical founders who want to ship.
    </p>

    <h2>What I do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Full-stack architecture (React, Next.js, Supabase, Convex)</li>
      <li>AI-assisted development workflows</li>
      <li>Technical SEO and automation (n8n)</li>
      <li>CTO-as-a-service for non-technical founders</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The Prompt Contract method</h2>
    <p>
      I developed <strong>Prompt Contract</strong> — a method to structure AI
      prompts like development contracts. Instead of hoping AI understands your
      intent, you contractualize expectations: stack, constraints, architecture,
      validation criteria.
    </p>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>
    <p>
      Find me on <a href="https://github.com/rentierdigital">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
